bug.short_desc: cannot mark task unread after incoming suppressed

long_desc.thetext: I'm not sure how I get into this state, but sometimes I cannot mark a task as unread (the command has no effect). It turns out this is because ITasksCoreConstants.ATTRIBUTE_TASK_SUPPRESS_INCOMING has been set to true for the task. The only way to clear this state is to get an actual incoming on the task.

Can you please give me more information how you get a task with ITasksCoreConstants.ATTRIBUTE_TASK_SUPPRESS_INCOMING.
When I have a way to reproduce this I think I can create a review with a fix.
Maybe it is only a test if ITasksCoreConstants.ATTRIBUTE_TASK_SUPPRESS_INCOMING is true and then reset this in TaskDataManager.setRead

I have steps to reproduce:
* use the org.eclipse.mylyn.tasks.core.synchronizationParticipants extension point to suppress incomings on a field * change that field in the web ui * synchronize the task * mark the task unread. nothing happens
Frank, I think you're right that clearing the flag in setRead is the proper way to fix this.
Thanks very much for looking into this, Frank! The change was merged.
